label.value: FFPE tissue paraffin embedding SOP

definition.value: A standard operating procedure for the paraffin embedding of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue.

label.value: FFPE paraffin processing for embedding temperature

definition.value: A scalar measurement datum that is the output of a temperature measurement assay performed during the paraffin processing for embedding in a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: fresh paraffin

definition.value: A paraffin that has not been previously used or recycled.

label.value: age of paraffin

definition.value: A scalar measurement datum that is the output of an age measurement assay performed on paraffin.

label.value: total time FFPE freshly poured blocks were cooled

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the result of measuring the total time that freshly poured blocks were cooled in the formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: FFPE tissue block handling, tracking, and storage SOP

definition.value: A standard operating procedure for the handling, tracking, and storing of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue block.

label.value: adherence to FFPE tissue block storage SOP

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates whether the FFPE tissue block storage SOP was followed.

label.value: comment on FFPE tissue block storage

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to storage of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue block.

label.value: comment on paraffin embedding of FFPE tissue

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to paraffin embedding of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue.

label.value: name of specimen slide preparation technician

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who performed a specimen slide preparation.

label.value: FFPE tissue section preparation SOP

definition.value: A standard operating procedure for the preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: microtome blade age

definition.value: An age that inheres in a microtome blade.

label.value: fresh microtome blade

definition.value: A microtome blade age that indicates that the microtome blade is as new as possible.

label.value: preparation of FFPE block face for sectioning protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the preparation on the faced block prior to sectioning of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue.

label.value: description of glass slide charge

definition.value: A textual entity that describes the carge on a glass slide.

label.value: charged glass slide indicator

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates that a glass slide has been positively charged.

label.value: uncharged glass slide indicator

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates that a glass slide has not been positively charged.

label.value: FFPE water bath temperature

definition.value: A scalar measurement datum that is the output of a temperature measurement assay performed on a water bath used in a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: microtome maintenance frequency

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates the frequency with which microtome maintenance is performed and recorded.

label.value: daily microtome maintenance

definition.value: A microtome maintenance frequency that indicates that microtome maintenance is performed and recorded daily.

label.value: comment on deviations from microtome daily maintenance SOP

definition.value: A textual entity that states information about deviations from a microtome daily maintenance standard operating procedure.

label.value: water bath maintenance frequency

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates the frequency with which water bath maintenance is performed and recorded.

label.value: daily water bath maintenance

definition.value: A water bath maintenance frequency that indicates that microtome maintenance is performed and recorded daily.

label.value: comment on deviations from water bath daily maintenance SOP

definition.value: A textual entity that states information about deviations from a water bath daily maintenance standard operating procedure.

label.value: comment on preparation of FFPE tissue section

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E staining and mounting SOP

definition.value: A standard operating procedure for the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) staining and slide mounting of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E staining in oven duration

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the result of measuring the duration in an oven for the hematoxylin and eosin staining of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: oven temperature during FFPE tissue section H&E staining

definition.value: A scalar measurement datum that is the output of a temperature measurement assay performed on a oven during a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) staining.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E deparaffinization protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the deparaffinization method used during the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained slide preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E staining protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the staining method used during the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained slide preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E clearing protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the clearing method used during the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained slide preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: FFPE tissue section H&E cover slip protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the method for applying a cover slip used during the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained slide preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue section.

label.value: manual FFPE tissue section H&E deparaffinization

definition.value: A planned process involving the manual performance of the FFPE tissue section H&E deparaffinization protocol.

label.value: manual FFPE tissue section H&E staining

definition.value: A planned process involving the manual performance of the FFPE tissue section H&E staining protocol.

label.value: manual FFPE tissue section H&E clearing

definition.value: A planned process involving the manual performance of the FFPE tissue section H&E clearing protocol.

label.value: manual FFPE tissue section H&E cover slipping

definition.value: A planned process involving the manual performance of the FFPE tissue section H&E cover slip protocol.

label.value: comment on preparation of FFPE H&E stained slide

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to the preparation of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stained slide.

label.value: H&E staining equipment maintenance performed and recorded frequency

definition.value: A data item that indicates the frequency with which hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) staining equipment maintenance is performed and recorded.

label.value: H&E staining equipment maintenance performed and recorded frequency value specification

definition.value: A categorical value specification that is used to record the frequency with which hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) staining equipment maintenance is performed and recorded. Categories include daily, weekly, bi-monthly, and per SOP.

label.value: comment on deviations from H&E equipment maintenance SOP

definition.value: A textual entity that states information about deviations from a hemtoxylin and eosin (H&E) equipment maintenance standard operating procedure.

label.value: specimen randomization key ID

definition.value: A specimen barcode associated with the specific chart (key) used to randomly assign specimens to one of several distinct experimental protocols.

label.value: manager of human research protocol requirements role

definition.value: A role borne by personnel responsible for managing human research protocol requirements including but not limited to screening, obtaining authorization, consenting and/or enrollment activities.

label.value: transplant alert associated with specimen donor

definition.value: A textual entity that is a notification within a clinical data repository that a specimen donor was a transplant recipient.

label.value: serology alert associated with specimen donor

definition.value: A textual entity that is a notification within a clinical data repository that specimen donor serology results include positive infectious disease data.

label.value: data and time parent specimen ID was recorded

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time at which the parent specimen ID was recorded.

label.value: comment on tissue specimen processing

definition.value: A textual entity that states additional information deemed relevant for tissue specimen processing.

label.value: human brain biobank

definition.value: A biobank that focuses on the special requirements of the human brain with regards to preservation, handling, and analysis.

label.value: central biobank

definition.value: A biobank which receives its specimens primarily/exclusively from tissue source sites. Activities include receipt, some processing, production of slides/images of the tissue, storage, and retrieval/shipping of materials on-demand.

label.value: laboratory, data analysis, and coordinating center for human specimens

definition.value: A laboratory that specializes in acquiring human tissues and analyzing components such as DNA and RNA from them.

label.value: pathology research center

definition.value: A laboratory that performs a rigorous review of images of tissue specimens by a group of senior pathologists not involved in the specimen collection typically to evaluate and characterize the tissue (e.g., % necrosis).
